The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 FIH report on Indian hockey 

New Delhi: Associations running on outdated constitutions, financial woes, non-registration of players and poor coaching modules are some of the vices that continue to plague Indian hockey, according to an expert report. 

The confidential report by Bob Davidzson, the International Hockey Federation (FIH) observer, to Indian Hockey Federation (IHF) lists umpteen ailments that have been ruining the sport in the country over the years. 

Davidzson recently submitted the report to the FIH. Identifying 14 areas of concern, the report says that IHF and the Indian Womens Hockey Federation basically run on outdated constitutions which lack clear responsibilities and tasks of committees in place. (PTI) 




